"nano image.build"






this command opens an editor ,then add this script to editor 






"[virtual=x86_64,multiboot] boot = {
    startup-x86 -D 8250
    procnto-smp-instr
}

[+script] init = {
    display_msg "Hello, stranger!"
}
"


virtual=x86_64,multiboot → We are building a 64-bit QNX image using the Multiboot standard.

startup-x86 -D 8250 → QNX startup code; 8250 enables serial output.

procnto-smp-instr → The QNX kernel.

display_msg "Hello, stranger!" → Will print this on QEMU's serial console.


Save + exit:
Ctrl+O → Enter → Ctrl+X
